1) The system Requires Java 8(Tested on Java 8_u65)

2) Tools Required
    a) Stanford CoreNLP
        Link: http://nlp.stanford.edu/software/stanford-corenlp-full-2015-04-20.zip
        
    
    b) Stanford Lex-Parser
        Link: http://nlp.stanford.edu/software/stanford-parser-full-2014-08-27.zip
        
    
    c) Stanford POS Tagger        
        Link: http://nlp.stanford.edu/software/stanford-postagger-2014-08-27.zip
        Jar Files to be added to CLASSPATH:

    d) Rita Wordnet    
        http://rednoise.org/rita/rita.zip

    e) Wordnet
        Included in the Archive        
3) Add the fallowing jar files to the java CLASSPATH
    
            JAR FILE                                From the Archive
            
   a)stanford-corenlp-3.5.2.jar             stanford-corenlp-full-2015-04-20.zip
   b)stanford-corenlp-3.5.2-models.jar      stanford-corenlp-full-2015-04-20.zip
   c)stanford-parser.jar                    stanford-parser-full-2014-08-27.zip
   d)stanford-parser-3.4.1-models.jar       stanford-parser-full-2014-08-27.zip
   e)stanford-parser-3.4.1-sources.jar      stanford-parser-full-2014-08-27.zip
   f)stanford-postagger.jar                 stanford-postagger-2014-08-27.zip
   g)stanford-postagger-3.4.1.jar           stanford-postagger-2014-08-27.zip
   h)stanford-postagger-3.4.1-sources.jar   stanford-postagger-2014-08-27.zip
   i)rita.jar                               rita.zip
   
4)To add jar files to the classpath in Linux/Unix
    a) Open the Terminal
    b) Change the relative path in the fallowing command and run
         export CLASSPATH=$CLASSPATH:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/rita.jar:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/stanford-corenlp-3.5.2.jar:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/stanford-corenlp-3.5.2-models.jar:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/stanford-parser.jar:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/stanford-parser-3.4.1-models.jar:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/stanford-parser-3.4.1-sources.jar:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/stanford-postagger.jar:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/stanford-postagger-3.4.1.jar:/PATH/TO/JAR/FILE/stanford-postagger-3.4.1-sources.jar
         
5) Change the working directory to the project folder.

6) Compile the Runner.java using "javac Runner.java".

7) Execute the Runner class using either of the fallowing ways.
    a) java Runner input.txt
        It will give the output as which class the article belong to
    b) java Runner
        It will give the accuracy levels on test set(It will take few minutes to complete)
8) Sample input files can be found in "input" folder.
